	<h2>Antimicrobial prophylaxis against infective endocarditis

</h2>						
	<h3>Description</h3>
	
		
			<div id="shortSummary">
				<p>The advice in this NICE guideline covers:
Patients who are at risk of infective endocarditis, specifically:

	adults and children with certain problems affecting the structure of the heart (such as a replacement heart valve or hypertrophic cardiomyopathy)
	adults and children who have previously ...</p>
				<p class="read-more"><a href="Javascript: toggleSummary('shortSummary','longSummary');">Read the complete summary</a></p>
			</div>
			<div id="longSummary" style="display: none;">
				<p>The advice in this NICE guideline covers:</p>
<p>Patients who are at risk of infective endocarditis, specifically:</p>
<ul>
	<li>adults and children with certain problems affecting the structure of the heart (such as a replacement heart valve or hypertrophic cardiomyopathy)</li>
	<li>adults and children who have previously had infective endocarditis (whether or not they have an underlying cardiac problem)</li>
	<li>people having any of these procedures:</li>
</ul>
<p>- any dental procedure</p>
<p>- any obstetric or gynaecological procedure, or childbirth</p>
<p>- any procedure on the bladder or urine system</p>
<p>- any procedure on the gullet, stomach or intestines</p>
<p>- any procedure on the airways, including ear, nose and throat procedures and bronchoscopy (a test used to diagnose some lung problems).</p>
<p>It does not specifically look at:</p>
<ul>
	<li>people at risk of infective endocarditis who do not have heart problems (such as intravenous drug users)</li>
	<li>people having procedures that aren't in the list above</li>
</ul>

